com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.ota

类 AylaLanOTADevice

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.AylaDevice
      • com.aylanetworks.aylasdk.ota.AylaLanOTADevice

  • public class AylaLanOTADevice
extends AylaDevice
    AylaLanOTADevice is used for updating an OTA Image. Three steps are needed to update an OTA Image over LAN 1. Fetch the OTA Image Info from the Cloud service by passing the dsn. 2. Fetch the OTA Image file from the Cloud Service and store in the Android phone/tablet. 3. Push the OTA Image file from the Android phone/tablet to Ayla Device over LAN.

        public AylaLanOTADevice(AylaDeviceManager deviceManager,
                        java.lang.String dsn,
                        java.lang.String ssid)
        Constructor for this class.
        参数:
        deviceManager - the AylaDeviceManager that manages this device
        dsn - The DSN of the device
        ssid - SSID of the device. This is needed in case the Ayla Device is in AP Mode. If the device is already registered to the user and connected in STA Mode then it is optional.

      • reconnectToOriginalNetwork

        public AylaAPIRequest reconnectToOriginalNetwork(int timeoutInSeconds,
                                                 com.android.volley.Response.Listener<AylaAPIRequest.EmptyResponse> successListener,
                                                 ErrorListener errorListener)
        Connects the mobile device back to the Original wifi network. User needs to call this once OTA Image update is done.Also the status of the Image update is sent to Cloud
        参数:
        timeoutInSeconds - Maximum time to spend trying to reconnect.
        successListener - Listener to receive on Successful update of status after we have connected to Original Network
        errorListener - Listener called if we fail to join the network in the specified time period or if we are not able to send the status to Cloud
        返回:
        the AylaAPIRequest that may be canceled to stop this operation
